Mac O'Brien

Class Senior

Hometown Omaha, NE

Last School Omaha Central

Major Philosophy / Computer Science

Bio

Historical

Biography

2021-22: Earned all-SCAC honors by finishing third in the 1- and 3-meter events at the SCAC Championships for the second consecutive year … Captured three of the four diving events in season-opening weekend vs. Southwestern and Centenary … Placed second in each event at the CC Classic ... Member of SCAC Honor Roll for the third consecutive year.

2020-21: Earned all-SCAC honors by finishing third in the 1- and 3-meter events at the SCAC Championships … Won both events in season-opening victory over University of the Ozarks … Named SCAC Diver of the Week … Member of SCAC Honor Roll for the second consecutive year.

2019-20: Earned all-SCAC honors by finishing second in the 1- and 3-meter events at the SCAC Championships … Won the diving event in double-dual with Austin College and McMurry University … Second in the 3-meter and third in the 1-meter at the Phoenix Fall Classic … Captured both events at the CC Classic … Member of SCAC Honor Roll.

Before Colorado College: Four-year letterwinner in diving … Team captain his senior season … Two-time state qualifier and member of conference all-academic team … Named Central HS Male Student of the Year.
